gn=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ushakeyomen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shakey Omen</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_yellowspot.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Apprentice</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>4/19/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>2:27:07 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Mr. Taxi (Anon the Evoker)</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">My views from 212 days of /played time as a wizard (yes, I'm older than dirt).<br>
<br>
Since the first wizard hit level 29, the desire to slap on /anon has crowded the mind of every wizard, even more so than the druid. Why? Because in general, we have better port locations. G Fay, the hub of elven activity, with 2 close cities, and NK at the bridge (not in the boonies at a circle), being the 2 most used pre-Kunark IMHO.<br>
Translocate (bind) offered a new way to get somewhere, and even with that I noticed a decrease in offers, after all I didn't have to move. People all the time in EC now call out &quot;looking for translocate&quot; instead of &quot;looking for port to (wherever)&quot;. Ok, less business for druids, and less fees for a wizard. Now the other slap in the face, translocate (zone). Now we can port the target to a specific area, especially DL and G Fay.<br>
<br>
.... What does this mean? Simple. Even less business for the local druid, and port donations going into the toilet, because they think &quot;Hey, you don't have to move&quot;. Wizards, all I can say is this.... Put /anon on, or be prepared to mem Trans (zone) 50 times a day. You have just been degraded to a Free Taxi.<br>
.... IF you can buy the spell off a tank for 5k, because he thinks YOU need the spell. We don't. Don't bother buying this, if tanks want free rides, have them get you the spell.<br>
<br>
